u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":979,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/08\/06\/true-fasting-leave-bad-words\/","url_meta":{"origin":23295,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Sawm: True fasting is leaving sins, bad words","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 6, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Whoever does not leave evil words and deeds while fasting, Allah does not need him to leave food and drink.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1903 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24868,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/05\/27\/fasting-waqar-sakinah\/","url_meta":{"origin":23295,"position":2},"title":"Jabir on Fasting: You must fast from sins with dignity, tranquility","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 27, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Sulayman ibn Musa reported: Jabir, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cWhen you fast, then let your hearing, seeing, and tongue fast as well from falsehood and sins, and avoid harming your servants. Rather, you must have dignity and calmness on the day of your fasting. Do not make\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24889,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/05\/29\/mujahid-kadhib-ghibah-sawm\/","url_meta":{"origin":23295,"position":3},"title":"Mujahid on Fasting: Backbiting and lies harm fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 29, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Layth reported: Mujahid, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cWhoever is safe from two characteristics will secure his fasting: backbiting and falsehood.\u201d Al-Bayhaqi said, \"Just as one guards his fasting from what is not befitting, one must guard himself in the month of Ramadan to obey Allah as much\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28096,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/23\/shield-damaged-gheebah\/","url_meta":{"origin":23295,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Siyam: Sins of tongue damage fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 23, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu \u2018Ubaydah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cFasting is a shield, as long as you do not damage it.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Nasa\u0304'i\u0304 2235 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Mundhiri \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0639\u064f\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0629 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0651\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064f \u062c\u064f\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0629\u064c \u0645\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19450,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/03\/fasting-ramadan-three-days\/","url_meta":{"origin":23295,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Fasting Ramadan, three days a month","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 3, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cFasting the month of patience, which is Ramadan, and three days from every month is like fasting the entire year.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Nasa\u0304'i\u0304 2408 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/23295","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/